From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 19:22:01 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add compact record modifier (padding minimization)

Second increment of the C++MG 'compact' feature: the record-level
modifier now performs compile-time padding minimization.

Surface: 'compact' immediately before struct/class/union opts the record
into layout optimization, e.g. 'compact struct S { ... };'.

Mechanism (mirrors Randstruct.cpp): after the class-specifier is parsed
in ParseDeclarationSpecifiers, cxxmg::applyCompactLayout rewrites the
RecordDecl's decl chain via reorderDecls(), stable-sorting fields by
descending alignment (tie-break: descending size). This runs once the
record is a complete definition but before its layout is computed, so the
layout builders observe the optimized order -- no RecordLayoutBuilder
change is needed, and it is correct on both the Itanium and Microsoft
ABIs. No persistent RecordDecl state is added (RecordDeclBitfields is
full); the parser drives the transform directly.

The transform is conservative and skips unions, dependent records,
records with bases or a vptr, bitfields, anonymous members, and fewer
than two reorderable fields; a trailing flexible-array-like member is
kept last.

New files: clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h,
clang/lib/AST/CXXMGLayout.cpp (registered in clang/lib/AST/CMakeLists.txt).
Parser hook: a 'compact' case in Parser::ParseDeclarationSpecifiers.

Tests (clang/test/CXXMG/compact/, one scenario per file):
- compact-padding-minimization.cpp: compact struct is strictly smaller
  than its non-compact twin (24 -> 16).
- compact-already-optimal.cpp: already-descending order is preserved.
- compact-class-keyword.cpp: works on 'class', not just 'struct'.
- compact-union-noop.cpp: union is accepted but unchanged.
- compact-trailing-array-stays-last.cpp: layout dump confirms a trailing
  array stays last while the other fields reorder.

diff --git a/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..3e3fcf854
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/include/clang/AST/CXXMGLayout.h
@@ -0,0 +1,44 @@
+//===- CXXMGLayout.h - C++MG compact record layout ------------*- C++ -*-===//
+//
+// Part of the LLVM Project, under the Apache License v2.0 with LLVM Exceptions.
+// See https://llvm.org/LICENSE.txt for license information.
+// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
+//
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+//
+// This file declares the C++MG `compact` record-layout optimization: a
+// compile-time, opt-in transform that reorders a record's non-static data
+// members to minimize padding. It is the foundation for the optional `hot`/
+// `cold` field-placement refinements added in later increments.
+//
+//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
+
+#ifndef LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
+#define LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
+
+namespace clang {
+class ASTContext;
+class RecordDecl;
+
+namespace cxxmg {
+
+/// Apply the C++MG `compact` layout to \p RD: reorder its fields to minimize
+/// padding (a stable sort by descending alignment) and commit the new order
+/// through RecordDecl::reorderDecls.
+///
+/// This must be called once \p RD is a complete definition but before its
+/// memory layout has been computed (i.e. before the first getASTRecordLayout
+/// query), so the layout builder observes the optimized declaration order.
+///
+/// The transform is conservative and is skipped (returning false, leaving the
+/// record untouched) when reordering would be unsafe or pointless: unions,
+/// dependent records, records with bases or a vptr, bitfields, anonymous
+/// members, or fewer than two reorderable fields.
+///
+/// \returns true if the record's field order was changed.
+bool applyCompactLayout(const ASTContext &Context, RecordDecl *RD);
+
+} // namespace cxxmg
+} // namespace clang
+
+#endif // LLVM_CLANG_AST_CXXMGLAYOUT_H
